<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<ecoSpold xmlns="http://www.EcoInvent.org/EcoSpold02" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.EcoInvent.org/EcoSpold02 ../../schemas/datasets/EcoSpold02.xsd http://www.EcoInvent.org/UsedUserMasterData ../../schemas/datasets/EcoSpold02UserMasterData.xsd">
  <childActivityDataset>
    <activityDescription>
      <activity specialActivityType="0" id="e4b3a12d-1383-589d-995e-0789e401c44f" activityNameId="baa6c4e7-aed9-4e47-909a-7b59325a1fab" parentActivityId="d6d8f5ef-82c3-553f-bccb-7ad33f5ebec0" inheritanceDepth="-1" type="1">
        <activityName xml:lang="en">nickel sulfate production</activityName>
        <synonym xml:lang="en">Nickelous sulfate</synonym>
        <synonym xml:lang="en">Nickel sulfate(1:1)</synonym>
        <synonym xml:lang="en">Nickel(II) sulfate</synonym>
        <synonym xml:lang="en">Nickel(2+) sulfate</synonym>
        <synonym xml:lang="en">Nickel sulphate</synonym>
        <includedActivitiesStart xml:lang="en">The activity starts when the raw materials enters the process.</includedActivitiesStart>
        <includedActivitiesEnd xml:lang="en">This activity ends with the production of nickel sulfate. It includes the consumption of raw materials and energy, infrastructure use and emissions.</includedActivitiesEnd>
        <generalComment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">This dataset represents the production of nickel sulfate (NiSO4). Nickel sulfate is a highly soluble blue-coloured salt. Two forms of nickel sulfate are commercially available; hexahydrate (NiSO4*6H2O) and heptahydrate (NiSO4*7H2O). The main use of nickel sulfate is as the electrolyte in nickel electroplating baths. It is also used in electroless nickel plating, in catalyst manufacture, and in the production of other nickel compounds.</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="1">The data in this dataset were obtained via stochiometric calculations. The amount of energy and water consumed are estimated based on data from a large chemical plant (Gendorf 2016).</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="2">References:</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="3">Lascelles, K., Morgan, L. G., Nicholls, D. and Beyersmann, D. 2005. Nickel Compounds. Ullmann's Encyclopedia of Industrial Chemistry.</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="4">Gendorf (2016) Umwelterklärung 2015, Werk Gendorf Industriepark, www.gendorf.de.</text>
        </generalComment>
      </activity>
      <classification classificationId="28f738cc-bb73-48f8-b633-f83fb9bc5ddc">
        <classificationSystem xml:lang="en">ISIC rev.4 ecoinvent</classificationSystem>
        <classificationValue xml:lang="en">2011:Manufacture of basic chemicals</classificationValue>
      </classification>
      <geography geographyId="34dbbff8-88ce-11de-ad60-0019e336be3a">
        <shortname xml:lang="en">GLO</shortname>
        <comment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">The data in this dataset are not geography-specific. Some values are based on data from a large chemical factory located in Germany. These are assumed to be valid for this geography.</text>
        </comment>
      </geography>
      <technology technologyLevel="3">
        <comment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">Most of the nickel sulfate is a by-product of electrolytic copper refining (Lascelles et al. 2005). Nickel sulfate is also produced by dissolving nickel or nickel oxide in sulfuric acid. This technology is presented in this dataset.</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="1">Chemical reaction:</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="2">I. Ni + 1/2 O2 -&gt; NiO</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="3">II. NiO + H2SO4 -&gt; NiSO4 + H2O</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="4">Reference:</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="5">Lascelles, K., Morgan, L. G., Nicholls, D. and Beyersmann, D. 2005. Nickel Compounds. Ullmann's Encyclopedia of Industrial Chemistry.</text>
        </comment>
      </technology>
      <timePeriod startDate="2006-01-01" endDate="2023-12-31" isDataValidForEntirePeriod="true">
        <comment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">This activity represents a basic chemical process and does not really change in time. Some values are based on data published by the Gendorf factory and are from the years 2011 to 2015. The time period has been adjusted accordingly. For more details, see the comments of the exchanges.</text>
        </comment>
      </timePeriod>
      <macroEconomicScenario macroEconomicScenarioId="d9f57f0a-a01f-42eb-a57b-8f18d6635801">
        <name xml:lang="en">Business-as-Usual</name>
      </macroEconomicScenario>
    </activityDescription>
