      <elementaryExchange id="043f8698-3616-536e-9f0a-cea5f544f024" unitId="487df68b-4994-4027-8fdc-a4dc298257b7" variableName="sulfur_emissions_water" casNumber="007704-34-9" amount="0.00114777949151113" isCalculatedAmount="true" mathematicalRelation="((((1/process_efficiency)-1)*sulfuric_acid_input))*(32.06/98.072)*0.1" elementaryExchangeId="5ac2254e-6b60-45f5-a700-6e0b93f411c8" formula="S">
        <name xml:lang="en">Sulfur</name>
        <unitName xml:lang="en">kg</unitName>
        <comment xml:lang="en">Calculated value based on literature and estimates. In case of sulfuric acid (H2SO4), part of the unreacted volume is released as sulfur (S) as a part of wastewater. The efficiency of the waste water treatment plant (WWTP) is assumed to be 90%, i.e. 10% of the volume of sulfur on the inflow to the WWTP is released to the environment. 

32.06 g/mol is the molar mass of sulfur (S).
98.072 g/mol is the molar mass of sulfuric acid (H2SO4).</comment>
